summary:
Suggests Governments of Uganda and Rwanda make reparations for damage inflicted on civilian population (para 14);

Calls on parties to protect human rights and respect humanitarian law (para 15);

Ensures safe access for relief personnel (para 16);

Urges cooperation with International Committee of the Red Cross (para 17);

Reaffirms importance of international conference on peace, security, democracy, and development in the Great Lakes region (para 18);

Expresses readiness to consider measures in case of non-compliance (para 19);

Decides to remain seized of the matter (para 20).
